Secret Messages is an album by Electric Light Orchestra (ELO) released
in 1983 through Jet Records. It was the last ELO album with bass
guitarist Kelly Groucutt, conductor Louis Clark, and real stringed
instruments, and the last ELO album to be released on Jet Records. It
was also the final ELO studio album to become a worldwide top 40 hit
upon release.
